{
  "texts": [
    "In cases where a phase is predicted by one model but not the other, its confidence is set to zero for the model where it was not predicted.",
    "Following this aggregation, only phases with an average prediction confidence ≥ 40% are included in the final prediction.",
    "This cutoff was chosen to give optimal performance on the tests reported in this work (Supplementary Fig. 10).",
    "npj Computational Materials | (2024) 10:45",
